Package: easyRasch
Title: Psychometric Analysis in R with Rasch Measurement Theory
Version: 0.4.3.1
Date: 2026-02-05
URL: https://github.com/pgmj/easyRasch, https://pgmj.github.io/easyRasch/
Authors@R:
    person("Magnus", "Johansson", , "pgmj@pm.me", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-1669-592X"))
Description: Multiple functions to simplify the Rasch analysis workflow. From
    descriptive statistics to fit statistics, response category analysis,
    DIF analysis, targeting, reliability, etc. Makes heavy use of existing
    packages for Rasch analyses, such as eRm, iarm, mirt, and psychotree.
Depends:
    formattable,
    kableExtra,
    tidyverse,
    eRm,
    mirt,
    psych,
    ggplot2 (>= 3.4.0),
    psychotree,
    psychotools (>= 0.7-3),
    matrixStats,
    reshape,
    patchwork,
    ggrepel,
    glue,
    catR,
    hexbin,
    janitor,
    ggdist,
    foreach,
    furrr,
    doParallel,
    Bayesrel,
    rsample,
    doRNG
Imports:
    iarm,
    PerFit
